main event: An unidentified object was reported sighted in Hamilton, Ohio on 9 July 1966.
interesting points: The report indicates that there is insufficient data for evaluation., The observation was classified as Ground-Visual., The object was reported to be one in number., The object was seen moving in a northeast course., The observer described the object as a slightly flattened disc-shaped object reflecting sunlight, passing rapidly at unusual speed.
witness description: a 27-year-old male resident of Hamilton, OH
